problem:
设$A,B,C$ 为三个随机事件，且$P(A)=P(B)=P(C)=\frac{1}{4},P(AB)=0$，$P(AC)=P(BC)$，则$A,B,C$ 中恰有一个事件发生的概率为

A. \frac{3}{4}

B. \frac{2}{3}

C. \frac{1}{2}

D. \frac{5}{12}

solution:
$P($ 恰有一个事件发生 $) = P(A\overline{B}\overline{C}) + P(\overline{A}B\overline{C}) + P(\overline{A}\overline{B}C)$

计算每个部分的概率：
$$ egin{aligned}
P(A\overline{B}\overline{C}) &= P(A) - P(A(B \cup C)) \
&= P(A) - P(AB + AC) \
&=  rac{1}{4} - 0 -  rac{1}{12} + 0 =  rac{1}{6}
\end{aligned}$$

$$ egin{aligned}
P(\overline{A}B\overline{C}) &= P(B) - P(B(A \cup C)) \
&= P(B) - P(BA + BC) \
&=  rac{1}{4} - 0 -  rac{1}{12} + 0 =  rac{1}{6}
\end{aligned}$$

$$ egin{aligned}
P(\overline{A}\overline{B}C) &= P(C) - P(C(A \cup B)) \
&= P(C) - P(CA + CB) \
&=  rac{1}{4} -  rac{1}{12} -  rac{1}{12} + 0 =  rac{1}{12}
\end{aligned}$$

所以，
$$ egin{aligned}
P(恰好一个事件发生) &= P(A\overline{B}\overline{C}) + P(\overline{A}B\overline{C}) + P(\overline{A}\overline{B}C) \
&=  rac{1}{6} +  rac{1}{6} +  rac{1}{12} =  rac{5}{12}
\end{aligned}$$
